WEBVTT

1
00:00:18.619 --> 00:00:21.453
<i>(LIVELY ROCK MUSIC
PLAYING ON WALKMAN)</i>

2
00:01:01.728 --> 00:01:04.220
But how did I lose? My
bike's twice as good as his.

3
00:01:04.298 --> 00:01:06.358
Yeah. well. you see
that's the thing. Shawn.

4
00:01:06.433 --> 00:01:10.268
Sure your bike looks great with all
these ridiculous reflectors and gadgets

5
00:01:10.337 --> 00:01:12.033
from a year's worth
of cereal box tops.

6
00:01:12.105 --> 00:01:16.406
but Gus here focused on
what's important. hard work.

7
00:01:16.476 --> 00:01:20.174
I'm sorry. son. but he
just out-pedaled you.

8
00:01:20.247 --> 00:01:21.806
You understand?

9
00:01:21.882 --> 00:01:23.111
I think so.

10
00:01:23.517 --> 00:01:24.517
(RINGING)

11
00:01:25.285 --> 00:01:27.015
I've got it.

12
00:01:27.087 --> 00:01:30.888
I had the wrong song playing
that time. Best two out of three.

13
00:01:31.758 --> 00:01:32.953
(SIGHS)

14
00:01:48.208 --> 00:01:49.652
I know what you're
trying to do. Shawn.

15
00:01:49.676 --> 00:01:52.009
And it's not gonna
work. I'm not buying.

16
00:02:00.020 --> 00:02:01.921
Oh. it's on now.

17
00:02:06.326 --> 00:02:07.453
(GROANS)

18
00:02:07.861 --> 00:02:11.389
On three. One. two...

19
00:02:17.304 --> 00:02:18.795
Let go of my chair. Shawn.

20
00:02:18.872 --> 00:02:21.137
The wheels. they're stuck
together. Get off. Shawn.

21
00:02:23.844 --> 00:02:25.288
Listen. you two...
Did you see who won?

22
00:02:25.312 --> 00:02:27.338
I beat him. didn't I?
No. No. Two out of three.

23
00:02:27.414 --> 00:02:28.939
Ha! That means
I beat him. right?

24
00:02:29.016 --> 00:02:31.679
Unlike everyone else around
here. I'm not fooled by the fact

25
00:02:31.752 --> 00:02:33.550
that you wear grown-up clothes.

26
00:02:33.620 --> 00:02:35.465
have mastered the rudimentary
levels of communication.

27
00:02:35.489 --> 00:02:37.458
and somehow manage
to feed yourselves.

28
00:02:37.524 --> 00:02:40.153
I see you for what
you are. Children.

29
00:02:40.227 --> 00:02:43.595
So do me a favor and let
the grownups do their work.

30
00:02:44.564 --> 00:02:45.998
I think I have a boo-boo.

31
00:02:47.267 --> 00:02:48.667
(SIGHS)

32
00:02:48.735 --> 00:02:50.465
Speaking of boo-boos.

33
00:02:50.537 --> 00:02:53.871
you wouldn't happen to have any extra
unsolved cases lying around. would you?

34
00:02:53.940 --> 00:02:56.239
Spencer. there is just
no easy way to tell you

35
00:02:56.309 --> 00:03:00.269
that I consider you a waste of
this department's time and energy.

36
00:03:00.347 --> 00:03:03.146
Huh. I guess there
was an easy way.

37
00:03:03.216 --> 00:03:05.395
But. actually. I've got less
patience for you today than normal.

38
00:03:05.419 --> 00:03:07.285
See. I received an invitation

39
00:03:07.354 --> 00:03:11.223
to give a presentation
at Twenty-one-LES.

40
00:03:11.291 --> 00:03:13.851
Twenty-first Century
Law Enforcement Seminar.

41
00:03:14.695 --> 00:03:16.721
Oh. Yes. Oh.

42
00:03:16.797 --> 00:03:19.198
We know that better
as 21 Saint-Cent-LES.

43
00:03:19.266 --> 00:03:21.258
I like to call it 21 Cent
Law-Enfo-Summit.

44
00:03:21.334 --> 00:03:23.860
Go ahead. make jokes.

45
00:03:25.338 --> 00:03:26.362
We just did.

46
00:03:28.208 --> 00:03:32.043
You see. kids. I'll be presenting
the cutting edge technology.

47
00:03:32.112 --> 00:03:34.479
the modern tools
for the new detective.

48
00:03:34.548 --> 00:03:37.416
We're talking back-scatter
x-ray scanning. DNA sampling.

49
00:03:37.484 --> 00:03:40.318
sonic weaponry.
You name it. I'm...

50
00:03:41.822 --> 00:03:45.122
That's weird. I
could've sworn that I...

51
00:03:46.593 --> 00:03:47.856
I don't believe it.

52
00:03:47.928 --> 00:03:48.952
Don't believe what?

53
00:03:49.029 --> 00:03:51.555
My car. It's gone. It
was right there. It's...

54
00:03:52.566 --> 00:03:54.034
It's been stolen.

55
00:03:55.502 --> 00:03:58.472
Who would dare steal my car?

56
00:03:58.538 --> 00:04:01.702
Well. here's the good news. It'll
make for an amusing anecdote

57
00:04:01.775 --> 00:04:04.939
during your presentation
at 21 Saint-Cent-LES.

58
00:04:12.452 --> 00:04:15.889
<i>I know. you know That
I'm not telling the truth</i>

59
00:04:15.956 --> 00:04:18.949
<i>I know. you know They
just don't have any proof</i>

60
00:04:19.025 --> 00:04:22.359
<i>Embrace the deception
Learn how to bend</i>

61
00:04:22.429 --> 00:04:26.332
<i>Your worst inhibitions tend
to psych you out in the end</i>

62
00:04:32.472 --> 00:04:33.783
All right. just keep
your mouth shut.

63
00:04:33.807 --> 00:04:35.901
I don't want people to
think anything's wrong.

64
00:04:35.976 --> 00:04:40.107
Morning. O'Connell.
Schwartz. Dobson.

65
00:04:40.180 --> 00:04:42.091
Just rapping with the
fellas. Shooting the breeze.

66
00:04:42.115 --> 00:04:44.050
Sweet. Now they'll
just think it's 1974.

67
00:04:44.117 --> 00:04:47.952
Wait a minute. Is this a prank?

68
00:04:48.021 --> 00:04:51.856
Did you take my car? Is
this some sort of punking?

69
00:04:51.925 --> 00:04:53.951
To think that we
would stoop so low

70
00:04:54.027 --> 00:04:57.156
as to tamper with police-issued
property and defile the institution

71
00:04:57.230 --> 00:04:59.995
that is the Santa Barbara
Police Department.

72
00:05:00.066 --> 00:05:01.227
is an affront to our honor.

73
00:05:01.301 --> 00:05:03.167
(SCOFFS) I for one.
am greatly offended.

74
00:05:03.236 --> 00:05:05.102
And I. for two.

75
00:05:05.172 --> 00:05:07.573
I just don't see how this
could have happened.

76
00:05:09.276 --> 00:05:10.972
(WHISPERS) Did
you? (WHISPERS) No.

77
00:05:17.617 --> 00:05:19.279
Wait! I'm getting something.

78
00:05:19.352 --> 00:05:21.321
What Shawn? What is it?

79
00:05:21.388 --> 00:05:25.484
It's a trace on Lassy's
car. It's faint but clear.

80
00:05:25.559 --> 00:05:28.519
You were recently somewhere where
the security of your car was compromised.

81
00:05:28.562 --> 00:05:30.531
I'm sensing someplace posh.

82
00:05:30.597 --> 00:05:34.967
surprisingly upscale for someone
on half a civil servant's salary.

83
00:05:35.035 --> 00:05:38.767
As it happens. I dined at a very
exclusive restaurant last night.

84
00:05:39.773 --> 00:05:43.005
The type of restaurant
one would take a date to?

85
00:05:43.076 --> 00:05:46.069
Is old Lassy back in the game?

86
00:05:46.146 --> 00:05:48.706
It is none of your business with
whom I spend my personal time.

87
00:05:48.782 --> 00:05:50.614
Now you have to
dish. Is she blond?

88
00:05:50.684 --> 00:05:51.743
Brunette? Mail order?

89
00:05:51.818 --> 00:05:52.842
You sly dog.

90
00:05:53.854 --> 00:05:56.187
Please. I'm not gonna
engage in some sort of

91
00:05:56.256 --> 00:05:57.918
juvenile masculinity contest.

92
00:05:57.991 --> 00:05:59.152
He went by himself. Yeah.

93
00:05:59.226 --> 00:06:03.129
Her name was Polly Smith. 324
Sycamore Lane. We kissed. Ask her.

94
00:06:04.097 --> 00:06:05.395
Polly Smith?

95
00:06:08.735 --> 00:06:11.227
Whoa! Something
happened at that restaurant

96
00:06:11.304 --> 00:06:12.897
that led to your
car being stolen.

97
00:06:12.973 --> 00:06:16.432
I'm sensing red
coats and accents.

98
00:06:16.509 --> 00:06:18.034
The British? No.

99
00:06:19.012 --> 00:06:21.743
The valets. Check the
valet that parked your car.

100
00:06:21.815 --> 00:06:23.750
He may have used the
old key-in-the-putty trick

101
00:06:23.817 --> 00:06:25.410
to get an impression.

102
00:06:25.485 --> 00:06:27.511
Of course. that would
have been my first deduction

103
00:06:27.587 --> 00:06:31.888
had I not been overcoming
this blatant violation.

104
00:06:33.126 --> 00:06:34.526
I'm gonna get right over there.

105
00:06:34.594 --> 00:06:37.860
No. No car. Remember?

106
00:06:41.134 --> 00:06:44.866
You guys are so funny. Oh.
guess what? I just got a new car.

107
00:06:44.938 --> 00:06:45.997
Yours.

108
00:06:47.007 --> 00:06:49.306
Maybe we had a little
too much fun with him.

109
00:06:51.645 --> 00:06:52.645
Maybe.

110
00:06:56.716 --> 00:06:57.945
I have to pee-pee.

111
00:07:04.824 --> 00:07:06.224
Maybe I help you. gentlemen?

112
00:07:06.293 --> 00:07:07.503
The theft of police
property has occurred.

113
00:07:07.527 --> 00:07:09.607
I have reason to believe
the guilty party works here.

114
00:07:09.663 --> 00:07:10.824
Oh. dear.

115
00:07:10.897 --> 00:07:13.833
Well. rest assured. you have
our complete cooperation.

116
00:07:13.900 --> 00:07:17.359
I only ask that you keep your
investigation under wraps. you know.

117
00:07:17.437 --> 00:07:18.530
for appearance sake.

118
00:07:18.605 --> 00:07:19.629
Noted.

119
00:07:19.706 --> 00:07:21.384
Now. I'm gonna need to
sequester your main dining room.

120
00:07:21.408 --> 00:07:24.867
interview your entire valet
staff and possibly your bus boys.

121
00:07:24.945 --> 00:07:25.969
One moment.

122
00:07:27.480 --> 00:07:28.680
Yeah. he's gonna be a problem.

123
00:07:28.715 --> 00:07:30.411
I don't know. He seemed
pretty cooperative.

124
00:07:30.483 --> 00:07:31.678
Your work here is done.

125
00:07:31.751 --> 00:07:33.982
I'm getting my car
back soon enough. Here.

126
00:07:34.054 --> 00:07:35.920
But I'm warning you.

127
00:07:35.989 --> 00:07:38.067
if word of this little incident
gets out at the station.

128
00:07:38.091 --> 00:07:41.550
I will start making things very
difficult for you down there.

129
00:07:43.330 --> 00:07:46.892
You're saying you haven't
even been trying all this time?

130
00:07:47.634 --> 00:07:48.634
Goodbye.

131
00:07:54.107 --> 00:07:56.201
He's not gonna get anywhere
talking to those valets.

132
00:07:56.276 --> 00:07:57.608
They have a very strict code.

133
00:07:57.677 --> 00:07:59.455
I still think you're
thinking about the British.

134
00:07:59.479 --> 00:08:01.539
May have to roll my
sleeves up for this one. Gus.

135
00:08:01.614 --> 00:08:04.243
Actually. I may have to
take off my entire shirt.

136
00:08:04.317 --> 00:08:07.879
Please don't. Oh. Later.

137
00:08:12.759 --> 00:08:14.022
Hi. there.

138
00:08:14.094 --> 00:08:15.494
My name is Shawn Spencer.

139
00:08:15.562 --> 00:08:18.498
I am the head psychic for the
Santa Barbara Police Department.

140
00:08:18.565 --> 00:08:20.261
and I may need to get
a statement from you.

141
00:08:20.333 --> 00:08:22.495
More specifically. the word yes.

142
00:08:22.569 --> 00:08:26.165
Nice try. But I reserve the
right to refuse service to anyone.

143
00:08:31.911 --> 00:08:34.574
That's all right. If my
parents were visiting.

144
00:08:34.647 --> 00:08:36.673
I probably wouldn't
want to waste time

145
00:08:36.750 --> 00:08:40.187
meeting handsome
new strangers. either.

146
00:08:40.253 --> 00:08:42.848
regardless of how smart
or interesting they might be.

147
00:08:42.922 --> 00:08:47.951
My parents are visiting. That was
pretty impressive. You really are psychic.

148
00:08:48.028 --> 00:08:50.020
Sorry. I thought you
were just hitting on me.

149
00:08:50.096 --> 00:08:51.689
Oh. I'm actually

150
00:08:51.765 --> 00:08:53.709
much more interested in
going out with your parents.

151
00:08:53.733 --> 00:08:55.634
I love the Miniatures Museum.

152
00:08:58.605 --> 00:09:00.471
What was it you
needed to ask me about?

153
00:09:00.540 --> 00:09:03.840
Do you recall any
suspicious behavior

154
00:09:03.910 --> 00:09:06.311
from any of the valets
on duty last night?

155
00:09:06.379 --> 00:09:09.110
Now that you mention it. we had
a new guy who started yesterday

156
00:09:09.182 --> 00:09:10.393
but didn't show up this morning.

157
00:09:10.417 --> 00:09:12.943
Bingo. Going to need a
name and a phone number.

158
00:09:13.019 --> 00:09:14.180
Well. of course.

159
00:09:15.555 --> 00:09:19.322
And then I'll give you the
information about the valet.

160
00:09:25.432 --> 00:09:28.231
Get this. the valet's
number is actually a number

161
00:09:28.301 --> 00:09:31.271
to a pay phone
outside of a warehouse.

162
00:09:31.337 --> 00:09:33.806
Yeah. I don't know.

163
00:09:35.041 --> 00:09:37.219
I don't know if it looks like the
warehouse from <i>Blue City.</i> Gus.

164
00:09:37.243 --> 00:09:39.610
You're the only one that
remembers that movie.

165
00:09:39.679 --> 00:09:43.514
What are you. insane? Way more
people saw <i>From the Hip</i> than <i>Blue...</i>

166
00:09:43.583 --> 00:09:45.394
Look. I'm not gonna talk
Judd Nelson right now.

167
00:09:45.418 --> 00:09:48.855
No. Just meet me at the
station in an hour. Thank you.

168
00:09:50.924 --> 00:09:52.722
A warehouse? Sweet.

169
00:09:52.792 --> 00:09:55.392
There's always something happening
on the D.L. inside a warehouse.

170
00:09:55.428 --> 00:09:57.173
You staked it out. right?
I know you staked it out.

171
00:09:57.197 --> 00:10:01.601
Oh. it got staked.
Stook. Staken?

172
00:10:02.936 --> 00:10:04.302
Staked. right? Right.

173
00:10:04.370 --> 00:10:06.965
Right. That's... Yeah.
yeah. It got staked.

174
00:10:07.040 --> 00:10:08.517
You found out what
happened to Lassiter's car?

175
00:10:08.541 --> 00:10:10.134
A whole bunch of cars go in.

176
00:10:10.210 --> 00:10:13.374
but only boxes full
of car parts come out.

177
00:10:14.080 --> 00:10:16.549
Dude. it's a chop shop.

178
00:10:16.616 --> 00:10:17.640
That's big.

179
00:10:17.784 --> 00:10:22.017
Victims. I see victims
everywhere. It's horrible.

180
00:10:22.088 --> 00:10:24.319
Sawed off parts strewn about.

181
00:10:24.390 --> 00:10:26.416
fluid spraying in
every direction.

182
00:10:26.493 --> 00:10:28.204
Oh. dear God. Are we
talking about a serial killer?

183
00:10:28.228 --> 00:10:31.756
I can see the victim's
names. Accord! Look out!

184
00:10:31.831 --> 00:10:34.300
Get out of there! Escalade.
don't let him in the door!

185
00:10:34.367 --> 00:10:38.270
Oh. Camry. you
were too young to go!

186
00:10:38.338 --> 00:10:39.704
Are we talking about cars?

187
00:10:39.772 --> 00:10:41.468
Stolen cars?

188
00:10:41.541 --> 00:10:46.138
The signal's too strong.
I'm getting chopsticks!

189
00:10:46.212 --> 00:10:48.044
Chopped salad? What?

190
00:10:50.750 --> 00:10:52.343
Chop suey! Good God.

191
00:10:52.418 --> 00:10:54.887
<i>Wheelie and the Chopper Bunch!</i>

192
00:10:54.954 --> 00:10:56.354
Does that mean anything to you?

193
00:10:56.422 --> 00:10:59.290
<i>Wheelie and the Chopper Bunch.</i>

194
00:10:59.359 --> 00:11:01.294
Chop shop. It's a chop shop.

195
00:11:01.361 --> 00:11:07.028
Yes. And I see a warehouse. And
cargo containers. And a street sign.

196
00:11:07.100 --> 00:11:09.296
And a little mouse
named Algernon in a maze.

197
00:11:09.369 --> 00:11:10.803
Flower Street.

198
00:11:10.870 --> 00:11:13.738
Flower Street. That's down by
the tracks. We better check this out.

199
00:11:13.806 --> 00:11:15.035
(GASPS)

200
00:11:15.942 --> 00:11:17.911
You know you just
bought that. right?

201
00:11:22.348 --> 00:11:23.976
<i>(WOMAN CHATTERING
ON POLICE RADIO)</i>

202
00:11:38.598 --> 00:11:40.829
Looks like a slam
dunk. Mr. Spencer.

203
00:11:40.900 --> 00:11:42.232
Wally. there. is the ringleader.

204
00:11:42.302 --> 00:11:45.830
And all the evidence we need
to take him down is right here.

205
00:11:45.905 --> 00:11:49.205
I mean stolen parts. serial
numbers. shipment logs. you name it.

206
00:11:49.275 --> 00:11:52.006
Don't need to thank me.
Chief. Just glad to help.

207
00:11:52.078 --> 00:11:53.808
Don't thank him either.

208
00:11:53.880 --> 00:11:56.008
Well. if I can't thank
you. I can't pay you.

209
00:11:56.082 --> 00:11:59.314
Our pleasure. Oh. you're
very welcome. You are.

210
00:11:59.385 --> 00:12:00.785
You know this ring
was responsible

211
00:12:00.853 --> 00:12:03.345
for hundreds of car
thefts around town.

212
00:12:03.423 --> 00:12:07.155
Wally had operatives in places...
Mechanics. valets. car wash attendants.

213
00:12:07.227 --> 00:12:11.494
all copying people's keys and then stealing
their cars from different locations.

214
00:12:11.564 --> 00:12:13.642
Does it say anything in there
about them stealing loose change

215
00:12:13.666 --> 00:12:15.635
or switching the
presets on radios?

216
00:12:15.702 --> 00:12:17.500
'Cause that happens
to me all the time.

217
00:12:17.570 --> 00:12:22.406
Okay. Gus. Go ahead and put
your aluminum foil hat back on.

218
00:12:22.475 --> 00:12:24.706
I'm not paranoid.
Shawn. It happens.

219
00:12:24.777 --> 00:12:26.769
Anyway. I believe this
is a department record

220
00:12:26.846 --> 00:12:29.816
for the fastest bust
ever in a case this size.

221
00:12:29.882 --> 00:12:31.475
Truly. your most efficient work.

222
00:12:31.551 --> 00:12:33.179
OFFICER 1: Nice work. boys.

223
00:12:33.253 --> 00:12:34.482
OFFICER 2: Good work. Shawn.

224
00:12:34.554 --> 00:12:38.082
Oh. stop. That's so unnecessary.

225
00:12:38.157 --> 00:12:41.855
You know. I couldn't help
but notice that a certain vehicle

226
00:12:41.928 --> 00:12:46.366
belonging to a certain head
detective just happens to not be here.

227
00:12:47.634 --> 00:12:49.364
Lassy. we had the
boys from crime scene

228
00:12:49.435 --> 00:12:53.372
move your car up the street right
before you and the Chief arrived.

229
00:12:53.439 --> 00:12:55.032
You're in the clear. tiger.

230
00:12:57.043 --> 00:12:58.043
Thanks.

231
00:13:00.613 --> 00:13:02.741
Although. today is a
street sweeping day.

232
00:13:02.815 --> 00:13:04.860
Did we park on the east side
or the west side of the street?

233
00:13:04.884 --> 00:13:07.080
North side. No. no. no.
wasn't the north side.

234
00:13:07.153 --> 00:13:10.248
Yes. it was. I'd know. Shawn.
I'm good with directions. You're not.

235
00:13:10.323 --> 00:13:12.201
Gus. you have the bearings
of a wounded bumblebee.

236
00:13:12.225 --> 00:13:13.557
Why would...

237
00:13:16.062 --> 00:13:17.553
Uh-oh.

238
00:13:17.630 --> 00:13:18.859
We need to get out of here.

239
00:13:20.733 --> 00:13:22.759
Well. you're certainly
a unique guy. Shawn.

240
00:13:22.835 --> 00:13:27.864
A guy who calls the day he gets
the number and brings flowers.

241
00:13:27.940 --> 00:13:30.876
I stole the flowers
from table one.

242
00:13:30.943 --> 00:13:33.071
They're fake and they smell
vaguely of creamy pesto.

243
00:13:33.146 --> 00:13:35.115
but I'm pretty sure it's
the thought that counts.

244
00:13:36.949 --> 00:13:39.384
And you're good enough
to come and meet me here.

245
00:13:39.452 --> 00:13:42.251
my last free night
before my parents arrive.

246
00:13:42.322 --> 00:13:45.486
Oh. wrapping up this case
was a lot easier than I thought.

247
00:13:46.759 --> 00:13:49.923
And this is one of the biggest
strawberries I've ever seen.

248
00:13:49.996 --> 00:13:51.157
Impressive.

249
00:13:51.931 --> 00:13:53.422
I've been here all day.

250
00:13:53.499 --> 00:13:57.493
so what do you say we take
our dessert back to my place?

251
00:13:57.570 --> 00:13:58.629
I say yes.

252
00:14:02.508 --> 00:14:04.670
Was this too easy?

253
00:14:04.744 --> 00:14:06.406
I beg your pardon?

254
00:14:06.479 --> 00:14:08.345
Nothing. I'm sorry.

255
00:14:08.414 --> 00:14:09.414
Never mind.

256
00:14:12.952 --> 00:14:15.478
I can't believe how
quickly I nailed this.

257
00:14:15.555 --> 00:14:16.784
(SIGHS)

258
00:14:16.856 --> 00:14:18.848
Am I really this good?

259
00:14:18.925 --> 00:14:19.949
Excuse me?

260
00:14:20.026 --> 00:14:21.961
I mean is it possible that...

261
00:14:22.028 --> 00:14:26.022
No. No. nothing like this
has ever happened before.

262
00:14:26.099 --> 00:14:28.864
And nothing's going
to happen tonight either.

263
00:14:28.935 --> 00:14:31.962
How dare you think
that I'm easy? Goodbye.

264
00:14:32.038 --> 00:14:36.976
What? No. No. no. no. no. I'm
not talking about you. This is...

265
00:14:37.043 --> 00:14:39.171
This is something much worse.

266
00:14:39.245 --> 00:14:41.874
It's the first time I've
been wrong about a case.

267
00:14:45.785 --> 00:14:48.050
Gus. I'm telling
you. it was too easy.

268
00:14:48.121 --> 00:14:49.885
Why would this Wally
guy slip up by stealing

269
00:14:49.956 --> 00:14:52.255
a detective's car from in
front of a police station?

270
00:14:52.325 --> 00:14:53.965
That doesn't make
any sense. Sure it does.

271
00:14:54.026 --> 00:14:55.221
One of his guys got sloppy.

272
00:14:55.294 --> 00:14:57.092
Gus. I'm pretty
sure I saw him smile

273
00:14:57.163 --> 00:14:58.893
as they loaded him
into the squad car.

274
00:14:58.965 --> 00:15:02.299
What. he thinks going to
prison is dope? No. Come on.

275
00:15:02.368 --> 00:15:05.338
I think I solved the crime
I was supposed to solve.

276
00:15:05.405 --> 00:15:07.499
not the crime I
should've solved. Okay.

277
00:15:07.573 --> 00:15:11.738
You're not making any sense and I
happen to be busy. so if you don't mind...

278
00:15:11.811 --> 00:15:12.855
What are you
doing? What is this?

279
00:15:12.879 --> 00:15:13.956
What are you going somewhere?

280
00:15:13.980 --> 00:15:17.473
Yes. actually. I am. I
finally have a free weekend.

281
00:15:17.550 --> 00:15:22.045
Which means I get to use the Spa Utopia
package I won for being top sales rep.

282
00:15:22.121 --> 00:15:24.181
It comes complete
with town car and driver.

283
00:15:24.257 --> 00:15:26.502
Gus. you've been bragging
about that award for over a year.

284
00:15:26.526 --> 00:15:28.461
Why go now? Maybe
I kept pushing it back

285
00:15:28.528 --> 00:15:30.429
because I was always
working a second job.

286
00:15:30.496 --> 00:15:32.829
Like when I had to enter
a Civil War reenactment

287
00:15:32.899 --> 00:15:36.427
or when I was protecting a
sorority of pajama-clad coeds.

288
00:15:36.502 --> 00:15:38.403
You're actually
complaining about that?

289
00:15:38.471 --> 00:15:39.837
No. I'm not.

290
00:15:39.906 --> 00:15:42.171
But let's not forget about
the entire week I gave up

291
00:15:42.241 --> 00:15:46.474
riding shotgun to a cat. which. by
the way. was not a boy cat at all.

292
00:15:46.546 --> 00:15:47.912
That's some serious
stress. Shawn.

293
00:15:47.980 --> 00:15:49.608
I have to get a
deep tissue massage

294
00:15:49.682 --> 00:15:51.844
to work out all the
knots in my back.

295
00:15:51.918 --> 00:15:54.012
I call the big one Little Shawn.

296
00:15:55.188 --> 00:15:57.555
Okay. that's the creepiest
thing anyone's ever said to me.

297
00:15:57.623 --> 00:15:59.717
They have a blind masseuse
up there. named Gloria.

298
00:15:59.792 --> 00:16:01.727
I hear she works
wonders. I can't wait.

299
00:16:01.794 --> 00:16:03.592
What is it with
you and the blind?

300
00:16:03.663 --> 00:16:07.896
I remember you went crazy for
that blind sculptor that did your bust.

301
00:16:09.068 --> 00:16:11.162
That was Lionel Richie
in the video for <i>Hello.</i>

302
00:16:12.705 --> 00:16:15.641
Great. Now I'm gonna have
that song stuck in my head.

303
00:16:15.708 --> 00:16:18.075
Good. Goodbye. Shawn.

304
00:16:24.750 --> 00:16:27.743
Chief! We got to reopen
the chop shop case.

305
00:16:27.820 --> 00:16:28.964
I'm pretty sure we
missed something.

306
00:16:28.988 --> 00:16:33.449
First of all. we don't
decide to reopen cases. I do.

307
00:16:33.526 --> 00:16:34.550
That's what I meant.

308
00:16:34.627 --> 00:16:36.493
Morning. Chief. Morning.

309
00:16:36.562 --> 00:16:37.621
(CAR ALARM BEEPING)

310
00:16:37.964 --> 00:16:40.399
Lassiter. Mr. Spencer
seems to think

311
00:16:40.466 --> 00:16:42.244
we might have missed
something in the chop shop case.

312
00:16:42.268 --> 00:16:45.432
No. No. that's an open-and-shut
case if ever I've seen one.

313
00:16:45.505 --> 00:16:47.770
Sorry. Mr. Spencer. but if
you want to reopen the case.

314
00:16:47.840 --> 00:16:51.038
you're gonna need to come
up with some concrete evidence.

315
00:16:51.110 --> 00:16:55.070
We don't devote department
resources to personal whims.

316
00:16:55.147 --> 00:16:57.139
Carlton. I finished
the PowerPoint slides

317
00:16:57.216 --> 00:16:59.185
for your 21 LES presentation.

318
00:16:59.252 --> 00:17:01.278
This is official
department business?

319
00:17:01.354 --> 00:17:03.380
Oh. you're right. Helvetica
is a much better font.

320
00:17:03.456 --> 00:17:06.085
I know. See how the "M"
in double murder suicide

321
00:17:06.158 --> 00:17:08.093
just jumps off the page?

322
00:17:08.160 --> 00:17:09.321
Okay.

323
00:17:09.395 --> 00:17:13.025
Is there anyone left that I can
actually speak to about this case?

324
00:17:16.235 --> 00:17:20.172
Like I said. there's still quite
a few unanswered questions.

325
00:17:20.239 --> 00:17:22.435
Well. what can I say? You
guys got me fair and square.

326
00:17:22.508 --> 00:17:23.806
That's just it.

327
00:17:23.876 --> 00:17:28.075
What kind of chop shop artist steals
a cop's car and doesn't chop it up?

328
00:17:28.147 --> 00:17:30.378
It's almost like you
wanted to leave a trail.

329
00:17:30.449 --> 00:17:33.351
Leave a trail or don't leave a
trail. it wouldn't do any good.

330
00:17:33.419 --> 00:17:35.786
You guys caught me quick.
snap. mind of a cheetah!

331
00:17:35.855 --> 00:17:38.051
I was like. "What?" Cops
were like. "Wham! Miranda!"

332
00:17:40.626 --> 00:17:43.755
Yeah. Well. there's
still some questions.

333
00:17:43.829 --> 00:17:46.663
For instance. why haven't
you posted bail. Wally?

334
00:17:46.732 --> 00:17:47.791
Oh. it's all good.

335
00:17:47.867 --> 00:17:50.302
You know. I'm gonna just do
my time with good behavior.

336
00:17:50.369 --> 00:17:53.237
and go on with my life.
Till then I'm like. "My bad."

337
00:17:53.306 --> 00:17:55.775
And the court's like.
"Get in that cell." Justice.

338
00:17:57.610 --> 00:17:59.909
Okay. Let's try this again.

339
00:17:59.979 --> 00:18:02.949
GUARD: Prisoner
1906. visiting time is over.

340
00:18:03.015 --> 00:18:04.015
Got to go.

341
00:18:29.308 --> 00:18:32.005
Your massage therapist will
be right with you. Mr. Guster.

342
00:18:32.078 --> 00:18:35.310
In the meantime.
please relax and hydrate.

343
00:18:35.381 --> 00:18:36.381
Thank you.

344
00:18:38.150 --> 00:18:39.150
(SIGHS)

345
00:18:42.121 --> 00:18:44.681
Excuse me. Excuse
me. do you mind?

346
00:18:44.757 --> 00:18:47.955
Shawn. what are
you doing here? Sorry.

347
00:18:50.096 --> 00:18:52.258
Shawn. what are you doing here?

348
00:18:52.331 --> 00:18:55.426
Trust me. The way today's
going. I need to relax. too.

349
00:18:55.501 --> 00:18:57.436
I can't get the Chief
to reopen the case.

350
00:18:57.503 --> 00:18:58.503
I already...

351
00:19:00.606 --> 00:19:02.768
I already told you. I'm
not helping you either.

352
00:19:02.842 --> 00:19:04.743
You will when you
hear this. What?

353
00:19:04.810 --> 00:19:07.405
I visited Wally in prison.

354
00:19:08.147 --> 00:19:09.747
You went to the pen?
I went to the joint.

355
00:19:09.782 --> 00:19:11.793
You went to the clink?
According to the visitors' log.

356
00:19:11.817 --> 00:19:15.845
the only other person who dropped
by to see Wally was Jonny G.

357
00:19:15.921 --> 00:19:18.083
Who turns out to be the Jonny G

358
00:19:18.157 --> 00:19:21.594
of Jonny G's Bling It
On Custom Auto Shop.

359
00:19:21.661 --> 00:19:23.857
So all he's guilty
of is a bad pun?

360
00:19:23.929 --> 00:19:27.388
Hardly. First Wally gets
arrested for running a chop shop.

361
00:19:27.466 --> 00:19:32.200
then he gets visited by Jonny G.
who works in custom auto parts.

362
00:19:32.271 --> 00:19:34.706
Adds a whole new
angle to the case. Gus.

363
00:19:34.774 --> 00:19:38.768
Well. is Jonny G dirty. too?
What's the "G" stand for?

364
00:19:38.844 --> 00:19:40.437
Was Wally working for him?

365
00:19:40.513 --> 00:19:42.744
What other criminal
nonsense are they up to?

366
00:19:42.815 --> 00:19:45.182
Man. we may have just uncovered
the tip of the iceberg here.

367
00:19:45.251 --> 00:19:46.275
That's all you've got?

368
00:19:46.352 --> 00:19:48.651
That and this.

369
00:19:53.025 --> 00:19:54.049
It burns.

370
00:19:54.126 --> 00:19:55.890
Sitting here listening
to you right now.

371
00:19:55.961 --> 00:19:57.953
Little Shawn just got bigger.

372
00:19:58.030 --> 00:19:59.862
I beg your pardon? No. thanks.

373
00:19:59.932 --> 00:20:00.932
Fine.

374
00:20:03.502 --> 00:20:05.266
What time are you
seeing that blind chick?

375
00:20:05.337 --> 00:20:06.828
Gloria can't see me.

376
00:20:06.906 --> 00:20:09.569
Dude. I know how
being blind works.

377
00:20:09.642 --> 00:20:11.201
I mean she's booked. Shawn.

378
00:20:11.277 --> 00:20:14.873
I had to book with this girl
named Kelly. I hope she's good.

379
00:20:14.947 --> 00:20:19.351
Mr. Guster? Are you
ready for your massage?

380
00:20:21.654 --> 00:20:22.654
Kelly?

381
00:20:22.722 --> 00:20:23.917
Call me Kel.

382
00:20:26.792 --> 00:20:27.987
You know what. Kel?

383
00:20:28.060 --> 00:20:30.586
I forgot I have another
appointment I have to go to.

384
00:20:30.663 --> 00:20:31.961
Thanks for your time.

385
00:20:34.834 --> 00:20:36.200
(WHISPERING) Yo.

386
00:20:36.268 --> 00:20:38.965
Dude. that dude's shoulders
looked like two little baby heads.

387
00:20:39.038 --> 00:20:40.336
I know.

388
00:20:40.406 --> 00:20:43.137
Okay. I'll help. but I
must be back in two hours.

389
00:20:43.209 --> 00:20:44.753
That's when I booked
the isolation chamber.

390
00:20:44.777 --> 00:20:47.212
Sweet. We'll take your town car.

391
00:20:47.279 --> 00:20:48.975
You're not naked
under there. are you?

392
00:20:49.048 --> 00:20:50.846
Naked and unashamed.

393
00:20:50.916 --> 00:20:53.044
Man! I'll be outside.

394
00:20:57.990 --> 00:21:00.084
How are we gonna get this
information out of Jonny G?

395
00:21:00.159 --> 00:21:02.594
The dude thinks we're
customers. Gus. It's a perfect cover.

396
00:21:02.661 --> 00:21:05.130
I don't get it. Who wastes
money tricking out a car?

397
00:21:05.197 --> 00:21:06.665
It's frivolous and ridiculous.

398
00:21:06.732 --> 00:21:09.429
Not to mention. it compromises
the integrity of the vehicle.

399
00:21:17.676 --> 00:21:21.613
Yo. Shawn. Yo. looking
good. man. What's up. homie?

400
00:21:21.680 --> 00:21:23.444
Jonny G. how are
you? I'm good. man.

401
00:21:23.516 --> 00:21:24.984
This is my friend.
Ovaltine Jenkins.

402
00:21:25.050 --> 00:21:27.076
Oh. respect. What's
up? What's happening?

403
00:21:27.153 --> 00:21:28.153
Peace. man.

404
00:21:28.220 --> 00:21:30.883
Yo. check it out. Your
ride is fresh to death.

405
00:21:30.956 --> 00:21:32.968
I always do the last checks
myself. you know what I mean?

406
00:21:32.992 --> 00:21:34.903
Just to make sure it meets
specs. Know what I mean?

407
00:21:34.927 --> 00:21:36.967
Yeah. I do know what you
mean. You know what I mean?

408
00:21:38.497 --> 00:21:39.726
(TRILLING)

409
00:21:41.066 --> 00:21:42.295
What ride?

410
00:21:42.368 --> 00:21:43.859
This one.

411
00:21:43.936 --> 00:21:45.461
GUS: What? My car!

412
00:21:47.006 --> 00:21:49.498
Shawn! I told you it
was the perfect cover.

413
00:21:49.575 --> 00:21:51.407
That is fresh to death!

414
00:21:55.514 --> 00:21:57.449
<i>(HIP HOP MUSIC
PLAYING ON CAR STEREO)</i>

415
00:22:03.222 --> 00:22:05.157
This is a company car. Shawn.

416
00:22:05.224 --> 00:22:06.624
I have to visit clients in this.

417
00:22:06.692 --> 00:22:08.524
Would you relax? I can't believe

418
00:22:08.594 --> 00:22:11.758
you spent all our money from
the chop shop case on this.

419
00:22:11.831 --> 00:22:13.925
What? You couldn't
find any magic beans?

420
00:22:13.999 --> 00:22:16.230
A Jack and the Beanstalk
reference. really?

421
00:22:16.302 --> 00:22:17.531
You wasted our money.

422
00:22:17.603 --> 00:22:19.731
I reinvested in business. Gus.

423
00:22:19.805 --> 00:22:21.899
Once we figure out what's
up with Jonny G's shop.

424
00:22:21.974 --> 00:22:23.943
and re-solve the case.
we'll get another check.

425
00:22:24.009 --> 00:22:25.554
And you want to know what
we're gonna to do with it?

426
00:22:25.578 --> 00:22:26.855
Party like it's 1999?
No. We're gonna...

427
00:22:26.879 --> 00:22:27.972
Party. Shawn.

428
00:22:28.047 --> 00:22:29.071
Karamu? Fiesta? No!

429
00:22:29.148 --> 00:22:30.192
We're gonna spend that money

430
00:22:30.216 --> 00:22:31.660
turning my car back
to the way it was.

431
00:22:31.684 --> 00:22:32.684
All right.

432
00:22:32.751 --> 00:22:34.629
But I still don't see why
you won't drive it like this.

433
00:22:34.653 --> 00:22:36.417
Because it's embarrassing.

434
00:22:36.488 --> 00:22:37.512
Embarrassing?

435
00:22:38.224 --> 00:22:42.025
Dude. this is sweet.
This is fresh to death.

436
00:22:42.094 --> 00:22:43.926
If you won't enjoy it. I will.

437
00:22:43.996 --> 00:22:45.555
<i>(MUSIC PLAYING LOUDER)</i>

438
00:22:51.337 --> 00:22:52.862
What's up. ladies?

439
00:22:52.938 --> 00:22:54.873
Nice ride. That's hot.

440
00:22:54.940 --> 00:22:57.307
Thank you.

441
00:22:57.376 --> 00:23:00.505
You're hot! You're so hot!

442
00:23:02.481 --> 00:23:03.574
Get out of my seat.

443
00:23:03.649 --> 00:23:04.793
You said you
didn't want to drive.

444
00:23:04.817 --> 00:23:06.809
It's my ride.
Shawn. I'm driving.

445
00:23:07.920 --> 00:23:08.920
Yeah.

446
00:23:20.699 --> 00:23:22.531
Just get us to the station.

447
00:23:22.601 --> 00:23:25.537
I got to convince the Chief to let us
snoop around Jonny G's operations.

448
00:23:25.604 --> 00:23:26.604
(POLICE SIREN WAILING)

449
00:23:27.039 --> 00:23:28.234
What now?

450
00:23:30.876 --> 00:23:32.538
<i>(WOMAN CHATTERING
ON POLICE RADIO)</i>

451
00:23:36.649 --> 00:23:38.914
I'm gonna need
your license and...

452
00:23:38.984 --> 00:23:43.217
Oh. hey. Oops. I didn't
know it was you guys.

453
00:23:43.289 --> 00:23:46.123
Sorry. but in this car you
just happened to fit a profile.

454
00:23:47.760 --> 00:23:49.991
I'm really sorry to
bother you guys.

455
00:23:52.965 --> 00:23:55.594
Mauler! Heel! Heel!

456
00:23:56.702 --> 00:24:00.764
Now I'm really. really sorry.
He's just a trainee for K-9 unit.

457
00:24:00.839 --> 00:24:04.503
Obviously. he's not gonna
make it. Sorry again. fellas.

458
00:24:04.576 --> 00:24:09.139
And. Gus. Mauler barks at
all cars. Not just blue ones.

459
00:24:09.682 --> 00:24:10.682
Uh-huh.

460
00:24:12.217 --> 00:24:13.685
JULIET: Carlton. it's here.

461
00:24:14.820 --> 00:24:16.998
Is this the new nano-material
vest we ordered for 21 LES?

462
00:24:17.022 --> 00:24:18.991
Yes. It's gonna kill.

463
00:24:19.058 --> 00:24:21.618
The Kev-Tech 7000 is made
with nano-material polymers

464
00:24:21.694 --> 00:24:24.926
that give it enough strength
to stop a tank mortar shell.

465
00:24:24.997 --> 00:24:26.625
I can't wait to try it out.

466
00:24:26.699 --> 00:24:27.699
Oh. no. no. no.

467
00:24:27.766 --> 00:24:30.167
The last time you got to be
incapacitated by the sonic gun.

468
00:24:30.235 --> 00:24:31.498
Now. it's my turn.

469
00:24:33.772 --> 00:24:35.365
Let go. O'Hara. Oh. come on.

470
00:24:35.441 --> 00:24:37.171
Okay. drop... Drop
it! Just let me try it.

471
00:24:37.242 --> 00:24:39.905
I've had just about
enough of the two of you.

472
00:24:39.979 --> 00:24:42.710
You can both be shot.
just sign the waivers.

473
00:24:43.549 --> 00:24:47.816
(CUCKOOING)

474
00:24:49.021 --> 00:24:51.650
Sonny was a cuckoo bird.

475
00:24:51.724 --> 00:24:54.284
Clearly he was
cuckoo for something.

476
00:24:54.360 --> 00:24:56.124
Cocoa Puffs. Exactly.

477
00:24:56.195 --> 00:24:57.635
I always thought it
was Cuckoo Puffs.

478
00:24:57.696 --> 00:25:01.463
No. Sonny is cuckoo for
the puffs. which are cocoa.

479
00:25:01.533 --> 00:25:03.445
That's why the milk turns
all brown and chocolaty.

480
00:25:03.469 --> 00:25:07.133
Oh. I was never allowed to
eat that stuff when I was a kid.

481
00:25:07.206 --> 00:25:08.970
That's why I don't
have any cavities.

482
00:25:09.041 --> 00:25:11.442
(CLEARS THROAT)
So. are we having cereal?

483
00:25:11.510 --> 00:25:13.411
Yes. But I'm getting more.

484
00:25:15.080 --> 00:25:20.986
9459687. 7635452. 250960.

485
00:25:21.053 --> 00:25:22.077
Are these serial numbers?

486
00:25:22.154 --> 00:25:23.281
Yes. but there's more.

487
00:25:23.355 --> 00:25:27.019
I see shiny rims.
spoilers. hammered rims...

488
00:25:27.092 --> 00:25:28.822
Spencer. is this
about the chop shop?

489
00:25:28.894 --> 00:25:30.105
'Cause we told you
the case is closed.

490
00:25:30.129 --> 00:25:33.861
Now. hold on. This is
very specific information.

491
00:25:34.800 --> 00:25:35.824
(SIGHS)

492
00:25:35.901 --> 00:25:37.501
O'Hara. run the
numbers by the crime lab.

493
00:25:37.536 --> 00:25:39.801
just to make sure we didn't
miss anything in the sweep.

494
00:25:39.872 --> 00:25:42.774
And you better not be wasting
department time. Mr. Spencer.

495
00:25:42.841 --> 00:25:45.041
Because if you are. we'll be
using this new vest on you.

496
00:25:45.077 --> 00:25:46.443
That's a great idea. Thank you.

497
00:25:46.512 --> 00:25:49.778
Because that way it's a plus
for me whether they work or fail.

498
00:25:53.018 --> 00:25:55.218
It better not take long for
Juliet to run those numbers.

499
00:25:55.254 --> 00:25:56.278
It won't.

500
00:25:56.355 --> 00:25:59.792
I already missed all of yesterday
on this already solved case.

501
00:25:59.858 --> 00:26:02.293
This is my last day to enjoy
my vacation. You don't realize

502
00:26:02.361 --> 00:26:05.024
how much stress I've
been under these past few...

503
00:26:05.097 --> 00:26:06.395
<i>(HIP HOP MUSIC PLAYING)</i>

504
00:26:07.032 --> 00:26:09.934
I'm not playing. Shawn. I never
get to do anything for myself!

505
00:26:10.002 --> 00:26:11.334
I'm getting that massage.

506
00:26:11.403 --> 00:26:14.032
And. yes. I'll be naked and
unashamed under my robe

507
00:26:14.106 --> 00:26:16.075
while they rub
Little Shawn down!

508
00:26:21.080 --> 00:26:22.810
Wait. it wasn't like that!

509
00:26:24.616 --> 00:26:25.616
(GRUNTING)

510
00:26:27.052 --> 00:26:28.052
(CELL PHONE RINGING)

511
00:26:29.721 --> 00:26:31.849
Jules. what do you got
on those serial numbers?

512
00:26:31.924 --> 00:26:35.053
Well. the good news is they
tracked them to car parts.

513
00:26:35.127 --> 00:26:38.791
The bad news is. the parts were
purchased legitimately for Bling It On.

514
00:26:38.864 --> 00:26:40.765
And the even worse news

515
00:26:40.833 --> 00:26:43.268
is that Lassiter wants to
know what size vest you wear.

516
00:26:43.769 --> 00:26:47.001
Very funny. Thanks for
making my life more challenging.

517
00:26:48.207 --> 00:26:49.971
The car parts at
the shop are legit?

518
00:26:50.042 --> 00:26:51.374
Looks that way.

519
00:26:51.443 --> 00:26:53.721
There must be something else
going on down there that we're missing.

520
00:26:53.745 --> 00:26:55.509
besides selling
stolen car parts.

521
00:26:55.581 --> 00:26:57.846
We got to get back down
there and look for clues.

522
00:26:57.916 --> 00:27:00.545
I don't know about you.
but I'm still on vacation.

523
00:27:05.691 --> 00:27:07.489
Uh-oh. Looks like
something's wrong

524
00:27:07.559 --> 00:27:11.394
with your in-dash DVD navigation
and integrated surround-sound-system.

525
00:27:11.463 --> 00:27:14.763
That was my speedometer.
Now. I can't see how fast I'm going.

526
00:27:14.833 --> 00:27:18.292
Regardless. we've got to
take it back to Jonny G to fix.

527
00:27:24.109 --> 00:27:25.668
Hey. dude. is Jonny G around?

528
00:27:25.744 --> 00:27:28.304
Don't know. We've been busy.

529
00:27:28.380 --> 00:27:29.678
What are you working on there?

530
00:27:29.748 --> 00:27:32.047
Getting this fleet
ready to ship to Arizona.

531
00:27:35.420 --> 00:27:38.948
Okay. thanks. And stealth mode.

532
00:27:44.329 --> 00:27:45.627
What are we looking for. anyway?

533
00:27:45.697 --> 00:27:48.132
Anything that points
to criminal activity.

534
00:27:48.200 --> 00:27:50.829
You know. a white cloth
sack with a green dollar sign.

535
00:27:50.903 --> 00:27:53.634
A red barrel labeled
TNT. An anvil. anything.

536
00:27:56.175 --> 00:27:57.199
Check this out.

537
00:27:57.276 --> 00:27:58.453
What. you already
have something?

538
00:27:58.477 --> 00:28:01.174
The point of those examples was
to imply it wouldn't be so obvious.

539
00:28:01.246 --> 00:28:02.942
Look how light it is.

540
00:28:03.015 --> 00:28:05.507
Awesome. Flava Flav
can wear it around his neck.

541
00:28:05.584 --> 00:28:08.019
Flav wears clocks.
not rims. Shawn.

542
00:28:08.620 --> 00:28:09.713
(CELL PHONE RINGING)

543
00:28:10.622 --> 00:28:12.250
Why didn't you put
your phone on vibrate?

544
00:28:13.458 --> 00:28:17.828
Dad. this is not a good... Whoa.
whoa. whoa. whoa. Okay. relax.

545
00:28:19.531 --> 00:28:21.523
I will be right there.

546
00:28:21.600 --> 00:28:22.624
We got to go.

547
00:28:22.701 --> 00:28:25.102
Go? We either need to
be working on this case

548
00:28:25.170 --> 00:28:26.729
or I need to be
back on my vacation.

549
00:28:26.805 --> 00:28:28.082
He said he needed
me there immediately.

550
00:28:28.106 --> 00:28:30.871
I've never heard him sound this
urgent. I hope everything's okay.

551
00:28:33.979 --> 00:28:35.379
HENRY: Here. Scale.

552
00:28:36.014 --> 00:28:38.142
This was the urgent emergency?

553
00:28:38.217 --> 00:28:39.241
Yeah.

554
00:28:39.318 --> 00:28:41.296
Got to get these on the
grill before it's too late.

555
00:28:41.320 --> 00:28:43.846
I can't believe you had me
rush down here for this. Dad.

556
00:28:43.922 --> 00:28:46.267
I thought something was actually
wrong with you. What's wrong with you?

557
00:28:46.291 --> 00:28:47.735
You do remember how to
scale. don't you. Shawn?

558
00:28:47.759 --> 00:28:49.352
Yes. I remember how to scale.

559
00:28:49.428 --> 00:28:51.454
You only made me do it
a thousand times as a kid.

560
00:28:51.530 --> 00:28:53.931
A kid who didn't believe in
animal cruelty. by the way.

561
00:28:53.999 --> 00:28:57.299
Well. those animals would've
killed you dead given the means.

562
00:28:57.369 --> 00:29:00.134
All right. you scrape the
scales. you don't bruise the flesh.

563
00:29:00.205 --> 00:29:02.231
You make an incision
around the gill and you filet.

564
00:29:02.307 --> 00:29:03.639
Down the spine.

565
00:29:04.343 --> 00:29:06.835
Ah. very good. You do remember.

566
00:29:06.912 --> 00:29:10.314
And. Gus. you remember
where the bathroom is.

567
00:29:12.884 --> 00:29:15.752
You're taking me away from
very important work right now.

568
00:29:15.821 --> 00:29:18.099
I'll have you know I'm on the
verge of uncovering something big.

569
00:29:18.123 --> 00:29:19.682
really big. huge.

570
00:29:23.595 --> 00:29:25.427
Did you ever have a
case you couldn't crack?

571
00:29:26.832 --> 00:29:29.961
Yeah. Yeah. sure. Of
course. More than a few.

572
00:29:30.035 --> 00:29:32.027
But a good detective
learns the most

573
00:29:32.104 --> 00:29:33.384
when he doesn't get the bad guy.

574
00:29:33.438 --> 00:29:34.462
No. I got the bad guy.

575
00:29:34.539 --> 00:29:36.735
Oh. well. sometimes he gets off.

576
00:29:36.808 --> 00:29:38.808
But a good detective
doesn't let that get him down.

577
00:29:38.877 --> 00:29:40.345
No. he's still in jail.

578
00:29:40.412 --> 00:29:43.610
Matter of fact. Chief Vick
even says it's my best work.

579
00:29:43.682 --> 00:29:45.275
All right. then
what's the problem?

580
00:29:45.350 --> 00:29:47.910
It doesn't feel like my
best work. you know?

581
00:29:47.986 --> 00:29:52.754
It feels too easy. Did you
ever have that problem?

582
00:29:56.061 --> 00:29:59.623
No. Shawn. I don't recall
any champagne problems

583
00:29:59.698 --> 00:30:03.362
like things being too easy.

584
00:30:04.236 --> 00:30:05.295
I don't know.

585
00:30:05.370 --> 00:30:08.670
I just imagine my best work would
be more complicated. you know?

586
00:30:08.740 --> 00:30:14.509
More intricate. important
and just more. you know. more.

587
00:30:14.579 --> 00:30:15.706
As always.

588
00:30:15.781 --> 00:30:18.444
you go after something for
the flash. for the excitement.

589
00:30:18.517 --> 00:30:20.428
and when you finally get
it. you're never satisfied.

590
00:30:20.452 --> 00:30:21.715
It always needs something more.

591
00:30:21.787 --> 00:30:23.153
That is categorically untrue.

592
00:30:23.221 --> 00:30:24.621
Your best case.
what does it need?

593
00:30:24.690 --> 00:30:25.749
It needs more excitement.

594
00:30:25.824 --> 00:30:28.419
Your first bike. what did
it need? More reflectors.

595
00:30:28.493 --> 00:30:29.704
Well. Shawn. did you
ever stop and think

596
00:30:29.728 --> 00:30:32.220
that maybe it's your
expectations that need to change?

597
00:30:32.297 --> 00:30:34.391
Son. look at me. Look. Shawn.

598
00:30:34.466 --> 00:30:38.198
Sometimes a case is just a case.

599
00:30:39.971 --> 00:30:41.769
(BARKING)

600
00:30:41.840 --> 00:30:43.809
He's just a
trainee for K-9 unit.

601
00:30:43.875 --> 00:30:46.538
Wait a second. wait a
second. I just figured it out.

602
00:30:46.611 --> 00:30:48.443
Wait. wait. don't.
Shawn. don't do this.

603
00:30:48.513 --> 00:30:49.857
Oh. this is much
bigger than we thought.

604
00:30:49.881 --> 00:30:51.315
And I was right all along.

605
00:30:51.383 --> 00:30:53.978
Shawn. don't you dare. Don't
you dare learn a wrong lesson

606
00:30:54.052 --> 00:30:56.612
while I'm trying to
teach you a right lesson.

607
00:30:57.489 --> 00:30:58.489
Look how light it is.

608
00:30:58.557 --> 00:31:00.201
We're getting this fleet
ready to ship to Arizona.

609
00:31:00.225 --> 00:31:02.585
Shawn. stop. stop. stop.
stop. stop trying to figure it out.

610
00:31:02.627 --> 00:31:05.222
Stop jumping! I can't
help it. It all makes sense.

611
00:31:05.297 --> 00:31:07.129
Gus. we gotta go!
I'll explain on the way.

612
00:31:07.199 --> 00:31:10.294
Shawn. Shawn. you should
be happy with a job well done

613
00:31:10.369 --> 00:31:13.305
regardless of the
excitement that it produces.

614
00:31:13.372 --> 00:31:14.772
Is that it?

615
00:31:14.840 --> 00:31:16.274
Yeah. that's it.

616
00:31:18.176 --> 00:31:20.236
Is it a tight knot right
under the shoulder blade?

617
00:31:20.312 --> 00:31:21.575
Yeah. How did you know?

618
00:31:21.646 --> 00:31:22.646
SHAWN: Gus!

619
00:31:25.350 --> 00:31:28.445
Jonny G is smuggling drugs
out of state inside of car parts.

620
00:31:28.520 --> 00:31:30.531
That's why those rims at
the office were so light. dude.

621
00:31:30.555 --> 00:31:32.922
They were hollow. That's
how he gets the drugs out.

622
00:31:32.991 --> 00:31:34.836
And some of that residue
must have gotten on your car.

623
00:31:34.860 --> 00:31:37.796
which is why that police dog
went crazy barking at the wheels.

624
00:31:37.863 --> 00:31:39.674
That's what Wally's
been covering for all along.

625
00:31:39.698 --> 00:31:42.293
He's just a fall guy. Jonny
G's running the real operation.

626
00:31:42.367 --> 00:31:44.165
Drug trafficking.

627
00:31:44.236 --> 00:31:45.636
We need to make
it back to that shop

628
00:31:45.670 --> 00:31:49.607
before the evidence
leaves for Arizona. Let's go!

629
00:31:53.745 --> 00:31:54.745
Damn it. We're too late.

630
00:31:54.813 --> 00:31:55.837
Somebody's here.

631
00:31:55.914 --> 00:31:59.578
(COMPRESSOR
HUMMING) Oh. Jonny G!

632
00:31:59.651 --> 00:32:01.142
Yo. Jonny!

633
00:32:06.258 --> 00:32:07.385
Yoo-hoo.

634
00:32:12.197 --> 00:32:13.790
(SCREAMING IN HIGH PITCH)

635
00:32:19.104 --> 00:32:22.336
Dude. his foot is still
on the accelerator.

636
00:32:28.780 --> 00:32:31.079
Stop. This isn't funny.

637
00:32:32.050 --> 00:32:33.245
You stop.

638
00:32:34.486 --> 00:32:35.681
I can't.

639
00:32:42.627 --> 00:32:45.153
The nitrous oxide
canister is open.

640
00:32:45.230 --> 00:32:48.257
Laughing gas? That stuff
is deadly in high doses.

641
00:32:49.568 --> 00:32:51.560
At least. we know what
the cause of death is.

642
00:32:57.409 --> 00:32:59.571
I can't believe Jonny
G went out like that.

643
00:32:59.644 --> 00:33:03.376
The police suspect foul play.
but so far they have no leads.

644
00:33:03.448 --> 00:33:05.679
All while I was on lock down?

645
00:33:05.750 --> 00:33:09.118
I guess I ended up with a
better sentence than Jonny G did.

646
00:33:09.187 --> 00:33:10.187
Irony.

647
00:33:11.656 --> 00:33:13.955
We still have a few questions.

648
00:33:14.025 --> 00:33:18.725
What do you know about a shipment
of custom cars on its way to Arizona?

649
00:33:18.797 --> 00:33:20.265
We were partners.

650
00:33:20.332 --> 00:33:22.777
but Jonny G was involved in a
lot of stuff I didn't know about.

651
00:33:22.801 --> 00:33:25.213
If I ask questions. he'd be like.
"None of your..." I'd be like. "Okay."

652
00:33:25.237 --> 00:33:26.237
Relegated.

653
00:33:26.304 --> 00:33:27.932
So. you're saying

654
00:33:28.006 --> 00:33:30.084
you weren't involved with
the custom car shop at all?

655
00:33:30.108 --> 00:33:32.737
I'm saying I was just a
front man for the chop shop.

656
00:33:32.811 --> 00:33:36.111
And now I'm doing my
time. but when I get out.

657
00:33:36.181 --> 00:33:39.982
crime's gonna be like. "Come
out and play. Wally. Come on."

658
00:33:40.051 --> 00:33:44.250
I'll be like. "No. Wally
doesn't live here anymore."

659
00:33:44.322 --> 00:33:45.415
Re-assimilated.

660
00:33:45.490 --> 00:33:46.490
(GUARD KNOCKING)

661
00:33:47.058 --> 00:33:48.082
Time's up.

662
00:34:07.312 --> 00:34:11.613
Dude. I'm starting to think
I was wrong about Wally.

663
00:34:11.683 --> 00:34:14.243
When? The first time
or the second time?

664
00:34:14.319 --> 00:34:15.514
Both.

665
00:34:15.587 --> 00:34:18.785
I think he's the mastermind
behind this whole drug thing

666
00:34:18.857 --> 00:34:20.416
and Jonny G's murder.

667
00:34:21.293 --> 00:34:23.285
Well. Wally was in
jail when Jonny G died.

668
00:34:23.361 --> 00:34:25.660
Yeah. He made sure of that.

669
00:34:28.567 --> 00:34:29.567
This is a little awkward.

670
00:34:29.634 --> 00:34:32.126
Yeah. Let's get out of here.

671
00:34:32.203 --> 00:34:33.933
Wally made it easy
for us to catch him

672
00:34:34.005 --> 00:34:35.598
because he wanted
to get thrown in jail.

673
00:34:35.674 --> 00:34:39.042
That way. he'd be locked up
when he murdered Jonny G.

674
00:34:39.110 --> 00:34:40.738
Which would give
him the perfect alibi.

675
00:34:40.812 --> 00:34:44.078
With Jonny G out of the way. Wally assumes
sole control of the custom car shop.

676
00:34:44.149 --> 00:34:45.310
And a secret drug operation.

677
00:34:45.383 --> 00:34:47.614
(IN FAKE BRITISH ACCENT)
Hello. motive. my old friend.

678
00:34:47.686 --> 00:34:48.710
Get this.

679
00:34:48.787 --> 00:34:50.221
according to
public court records.

680
00:34:50.288 --> 00:34:51.881
Wally posted bail this morning.

681
00:34:51.957 --> 00:34:53.357
Why wait until now?

682
00:34:55.360 --> 00:34:58.728
Dude. because the big
drug deal goes down today!

683
00:34:58.797 --> 00:35:00.095
But we don't know when or where.

684
00:35:00.165 --> 00:35:01.165
(SIGHS)

685
00:35:05.370 --> 00:35:08.772
Oh. yes. we do. Yes. we do.

686
00:35:08.840 --> 00:35:10.206
You call Fleet Feat Trucking.

687
00:35:10.275 --> 00:35:12.744
Find out if they're making
any custom car deliveries today.

688
00:35:12.811 --> 00:35:16.509
Find out when and where. I'll go get
Jules and Lassy. Dude. we got this!

689
00:35:16.581 --> 00:35:20.643
CARLTON: As you'll see the tools in
the arsenal of the modern day detective

690
00:35:20.719 --> 00:35:23.655
are formidable to say the least.

691
00:35:23.722 --> 00:35:26.021
Lights. please. Enjoy.

692
00:35:34.699 --> 00:35:36.565
I pretended to be
Jonny G's lawyer.

693
00:35:36.635 --> 00:35:39.195
got the trucking company to
tell me that a fleet from Bling It On

694
00:35:39.270 --> 00:35:41.466
is expected to be
dropped off at 2:30.

695
00:35:41.539 --> 00:35:43.337
I wrote the location down.

696
00:35:44.109 --> 00:35:46.738
This says. in the
middle of a field.

697
00:35:46.811 --> 00:35:48.279
Why did you have
to write that down?

698
00:35:48.346 --> 00:35:49.575
The address is on the back.

699
00:35:49.648 --> 00:35:50.648
Nice.

700
00:35:51.416 --> 00:35:53.146
We don't have a lot of time.

701
00:35:53.218 --> 00:35:54.413
CARLTON: Lights. please. No.

702
00:35:56.421 --> 00:36:00.722
Scientific advancements. and
the mapping of the human genome.

703
00:36:00.792 --> 00:36:03.853
and the manipulation of the
building blocks of matter itself

704
00:36:03.928 --> 00:36:08.457
have taken law enforcement
into the 21st century and beyond.

705
00:36:10.902 --> 00:36:12.063
Thank you.

706
00:36:14.239 --> 00:36:17.038
Thanks very much. So.
are there any questions?

707
00:36:17.842 --> 00:36:18.842
Yes.

708
00:36:19.978 --> 00:36:23.745
I thought you were gonna show
some new law enforcement techniques.

709
00:36:23.815 --> 00:36:25.716
We've seen all
these things on <i>CSI.</i>

710
00:36:25.784 --> 00:36:28.083
Well. I can assure you that

711
00:36:28.153 --> 00:36:31.214
this technology represents the
latest available to police departments.

712
00:36:31.289 --> 00:36:33.417
Oh. now you're onto
something. Lassy!

713
00:36:34.259 --> 00:36:37.286
Spencer? Okay. nobody
called for a psychic.

714
00:36:37.362 --> 00:36:38.660
Psychic? Awesome.

715
00:36:38.730 --> 00:36:41.461
I'm getting a reading
here. It's strange.

716
00:36:43.501 --> 00:36:46.096
Gus. what is this? I think
you may be magnetized.

717
00:36:46.171 --> 00:36:47.366
(GROANING)

718
00:36:49.074 --> 00:36:52.476
(GROANING)

719
00:36:52.577 --> 00:36:54.842
(SCREAMING)

720
00:37:00.919 --> 00:37:02.319
Give me.

721
00:37:02.387 --> 00:37:04.947
Right in the middle
of my presentation.

722
